    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010706.22" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="6">
        <title>HFCM (Horizontal Fuel Conditioning Module) Fuel Pump</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s305010706.22.1">
            <figure id="f3050107101" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31234.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>Functional diagram for the fuel pump</caption>
            </figure>
            <para id="s305010706.20.1.1"></para>
            <table id="t3050107208" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>The functional diagram for the fuel pump includes the following:</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Fuel pump</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Fuel pump relay</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Battery</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Ignition switch</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>The fuel pump is located inside the Horizontal Fuel Conditioning Module (HFCM)
                and is serviceable separately. The ECM controls a fuel pump relay that powers the fuel pump. When the
                ignition switch is turned to ON, the fuel pump relay is energized for 60 seconds. If the ECM does not
                detect engine running at the end of the 60 seconds it will de-energize the fuel pump relay and the fuel
                pump. The ECM monitors the voltage with the output of the fuel pump relay on the Fuel Pump Monitor (FPM)
                circuit.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.22.2">
            <title>Fuel Pump Circuit Operation</title>
            <figure id="f3050107102" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31235.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"/>
                <caption>Fuel pump circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The fuel pump relay is supplied power at Pin 1(86) from VIGN. The fuel pump relay is energized by
                ground supplies by the ECM through Pin X3-9 to Pin 2(85). Power is supplied to Pin 3(30) from the
                battery. When the relay coil is energized power is supplied to the fuel pump from Pin 5(87). The ECM
                monitors the output of the relay from the relay to X4-15.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection/Management</title>The ECM continuously monitors the output of the fuel pump
                relay; when voltage is out of expected range a DTC will be set.
            </para>
            <para>An open or short to ground in the fuel pump relay control circuit can be detected by an on-demand
                Output Circuit Check (OCC) performed during the KOEO Standard test. When a circuit fault is detected, a
                DTC will be set. Fuel pump and fuel pump harness problems can not be detected by the ECM.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Fuel Pump DTCs</title>DTCs are read using the EST or by counting the flashes from the amber and
                red lamps.
            </para>
            <table id="t3050107209" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 237</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Fuel Pump Control OCC self-test failed</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 237 is set by the ECM when the OCC test has failed after the KOEO Standard
                                    test has been run.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 237 can be set for an open or short to ground on FPC circuit, an open or short
                                    to ground on VIGNcircuit to the fuel pump relay, or an open fuel pump relay coil.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t3050107210" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 374</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Fuel pump relay circuit fault</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 374 is set by the ECM when the relay output voltage does not meet expected
                                    voltage.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 374 can be set for an open in the B+ supply circuit to fuel pump relay, open
                                    or shorted FPM circuit, or a failed fuel pump relay.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 374 can be set if there is a failed control circuit, repair DTC 237 first.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
